A Ukrainian naval drone carrying 450 kilograms of TNT struck a Russian Navy base at Novorossiisk in the Black Sea on August 3, causing extensive damage to a Russian warship, sources in the Ukrainian Security Service (SBU) told 
@svoboda_radio. 

SBU sources shared the video purportedly showing the landing ship Olenegorsky Gornyak from the perspective of a camera mounted on the naval drone that ceases its video feed at the moment of the alleged impact. The warship was seen tilted and being towed to dock on August 4.

Flood levels in Kherson on 7 June, filmed by 
@svoboda_radio

The water levels have risen several meters, trapping dozens of people in their homes and killing scores of animals, with health authorities warning of possibly contaminated drinking water after the destruction.

Kherson residents say that Russian forces used a pretrial detention center to interrogate and torture locals. 

Some say they heard screams coming from the building. 

@currenttime correspondent Borys Sachalko visited Kherson and spoke with people about what life was like under Russian occupation.
